annotationA: GH10112p; Necrotic is a hemolymphatic Serpin that negatively regulates a serine protease involved in the immune activation of the Toll pathway. It is thought to function at the level or upstream of the serine protease psh
annotationB: CG8539, isoform A; Zinc ion binding; metallocarboxypeptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proteolysis
